      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. They made it to the final round for a senior dev role here in Austin, so it's a tough one. They were really strong in system design and had great culture fit, but we just went with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. Can you draft something professional and kind so we don't burn a bridge?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for Senior Developer Position\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. We appreciate the time and effort you invested in the interview process for the Senior Developer position here at [Company Name]. We were impressed by your expertise in system design and your strong cultural fit within our team.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who brings a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. This decision was not easy, and we genuinely value the skills and potential you demonstrated during your interview.\n\nWe encourage you to apply for future opportunities at [Company Name], as we believe you have the talent and drive to excel in a role that matches your strengths. Thank you once again for your interest in our company, and we wish you the best in your career endeavors.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Position]\n[Company Name]\n[Contact Information]",
