    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's a good start but maybe a bit too generic? can you make it sound a little more personal and warm? i want them to feel like we actually liked them and that it's just a timing/skillset thing rather than them being unqualified. maybe add a line about how we'll keep their resume on file specifically for future cloud-related openings?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for Senior Developer Position\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to personally reach out to you following our recent interview process for the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. We truly appreciated the time and effort you invested, and we were delighted to witness your impressive skills in system design and your seamless fit with our team culture.\n\nAfter thoughtful deliberation, we have chosen to proceed with another candidate whose experience with our specific cloud stack aligns more closely with our current needs. This decision was not made lightly, and we genuinely value the unique strengths and potential you brought to the table during your interview.\n\nI want to assure you that your resume will remain on file with us, and we will be actively considering your qualifications for future opportunities that align with your expertise, particularly those related to our cloud stack. We believe that your talents and drive would be a great fit for such roles.\n\nWe truly enjoyed getting to know you and wish you the very best in your career journey. Please do not hesitate to reach out if you have any questions or if there is anything else we can assist you with.\n\nWarm regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Position]\n[Company Name]\n[Contact Information]",
      "source": "target",
